  <li>
    <p>He seemed scarcely to hear her, and was waling up and down the room <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="in earnest meditation"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(苦苦思索)</code></b>; <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="his brows contracted"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(眉头紧皱)</code></b>, his air gloomy.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Lydia – the humiliation, the misery she was bringing on them all, soon <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="swallowed up"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(吞没)</code></b> every private care, and covering her face with her handkerchief, Elizabeth was soon lost to everything else.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="Would to Heaven that"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(表示愿望)</code></b> anything could be either said or done on my part, that might offer consolation to such distress.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>For such an attachment as this, she might have sufficient charms, and though she did not suppose Lydia to be deliberately engaging in an elopement, without the intention of marriage, she had no difficulty in believing that neither her virtue nor her understanding would preserve her from <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="falling an easy prey"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(沦为唾手可得的猎物)</code></b>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>She could neither wonder nor condemn, but the belief of his self-conquest <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="brought nothing consolatory to her bosom"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(未能给她的心灵带来一丝安慰)</code></b>, afforded no palliation of her distress.</p>
  </li>
</ol>
